[Tip For Chords] 🎹 'Cook Gang' what up! 🤙🏾 Today's post can be beneficial to both my seasoned and novice producers. I was importing some vocal chops from @avidtechnology 's Pro Tools.. into @flstudio_software to manipulate using 'Pitcher'.. when I remembered another use for this plugin that you guys might enjoy!💡. When I'm having a bit of a slow start with my core melody.. I like to pull up 'Pitcher' to help jumpstart the vibe. This plugin comes stock with FL.. and can be found in the plugin/effects list of the 'Fruity Mixer'. To the left of the plugin.. I start by choosing what mood I would like to play in; 'Major' (Bright/Happy) or 'Minor' (Dark/Sad). Directly underneath this option.. I then choose the 'Scale' I would like to play in.. for example.. the scale of 'C'. This will highlight the notes in that scale that can be played together to form chords. The great part about this information.. is that you can mix.. match and even invert the highlighted notes to your liking. As a bonus tip: Click the drop down arrow located in the top left corner of the plugin. From this menu choose 'Detached'. This will allow you to keep 'Pitcher' up on your screen as a reference while you click around in the 'Piano Roll'. What 'hacks' do you guys have for creating chords?? Share them with myself and the 'Gang' in the comments below. Much love! #TrenchLord #CookGang
